<HEADLINE>
<P>
R. S. NEUSCHATZ; SERVED ON L.A. PARKS BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Royce Schaffer Neuschatz, former Los Angeles City Recreation and Parks 
commissioner and a regional planning consultant, died Saturday of cancer in 
Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
She was 56 and was on the faculty of the Department of Landscape Architecture, 
School of Environmental Design, at Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
Ms. Neuschatz was a regional planner for the Southern California Assn. of 
Governments from 1972 to 1975, helping coordinate open-space planning and park 
bond programs, and served on the Recreation and Parks Commission from 1978 to 
1984. 
</P>
<P>
She was an ardent proponent of parkland while on the commission, voting against 
efforts to establish a landfill in Griffith Park and the construction of the 
Gene Autry Western Heritage Museum at the same park. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service will be held at 10:30 a.m. Wednesday at the old zoo picnic 
area in Griffith Park. 
</P>
</TEXT>
