<HEADLINE>
<P>
MURRAY WAY OFF BASE FOR HIS DEFENSE OF ROSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What's the controversy? 
</P>
<P>
There's a simple rule in baseball and everybody knows it. You don't bet on 
ballgames. Pete Rose knew the rule; and if he ignored the rule, he has to go. 
</P>
<P>
No more megabuck contracts and $15 autographs. No more big league perks. He's 
not going to be special anymore, and for a guy like him, that's probably the 
worst punishment of all. 
</P>
<P>
ED HONECK 
</P>
<P>
STEVE ORTH 
</P>
<P>
Orange 
