<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARDINAL TIMOTHY MANNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times' coverage of the life and death of Cardinal Timothy Manning (June 24) 
proved three things to me. First, leadership means service; further, it means 
making a difference for the good of all humankind. Second, such "mild-mannered" 
leaders as Cardinal Manning are many times more profound than the leaders who 
take a more reactionary approach. Third, he was truly a good man. I hope that 
my epitaph reads the same. 
</P>
<P>
SHAUN DI ANDRE STRONG 
</P>
<P>
Brentwood 
</P>
