<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified woman who was walking along Interstate 5 near Fiesta Island 
Road was struck by a car and killed Thursday, authorities reported. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, who carried no identification, was walking north on the eastern 
shoulder of I-5 about 6:25 p.m. when she stepped into traffic, according to 
Deputy Coroner Ken Bell. 
</P>
<P>
A northbound car driven by Philip Kanish of San Diego struck the woman, Bell 
said. She was pronounced dead at UC San Diego Medical Center about 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, thought to be a transient, was described as black, 5-foot-6, 130 
pounds, in her early 30s. She was wearing a yellow pullover. 
</P>
