<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEGINNER'S LUCK HELPS BOLES AT VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It took a little luck and some hard driving, but Allen Boles of San Fernando 
won the 15-lap Street Stock main event at Ventura Raceway on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Boles, in his first race at Ventura, drove the one-fifth-mile dirt oval as if 
he had been driving the track the entire season. And a little bit of luck 
didn't hurt either. 
</P>
<P>
Street Stock points leader Charles Utts of Camarillo was leading the 17-car 
pack when a broken fan belt put him out of the race and allowed Boles to take 
charge in his 1968 Camaro. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Curtis of Camarillo edged figure 8 points leader Rock Ake, Jr. of Moorpark 
by half a car length in the six-lap Mini Stock figure 8 main event. With the 
win, Curtis' sixth, he ties Ake for the most figure 8 main event victories this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Webster of Camarillo was third. 
</P>
<P>
Curtis also won the 20-lap oval track main event. The victory was Curtis' 14th 
main-event title of the season, which reached its midway point Friday. 
</P>
<P>
John Christensen of Palmdale overtook Tom Stephens of Ventura on the final lap 
of the eight-lap Street Stock figure 8 main event to score his third such win 
of the season. Stephens and Don Famularo of Canyon Country finished second and 
third, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
Utts continued his winning ways earlier in the evening with a hard-fought 
eight-lap heat-race victory. Utts overtook leader Mike Johannes of Van Nuys on 
Lap 6 after working his way up from the back of the pack. Johannes finished 
fourth after hitting the backstretch wall on Lap 7. 
</P>
<P>
Phil Barrow of Oxnard and Boles finished second and third, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo's Jeff Bosley won the other Street Stock heat race. Paul Moore of 
Oxnard and Nick Magley of Ventura won the Mini Stock heat races. 
</P>
<P>
Sue Pittinato of West Hills captured the four-lap Street Stock trophy dash, and 
Curtis won the Mini Stock division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
