<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO-AM BASKETBALL LEAGUE TO BEGIN PLAY IN VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The L. A. Valley Pro-Am basketball league, an independent affiliate of the Los 
Angeles Pro-Am Summer League, will begin play Sunday at Chatsworth High. 
</P>
<P>
Two games will be played, the first at 6:30 p.m. The league, scheduled to run 
through August, with playoffs beginning in September, also will include games 
on Wednesday nights at Sylmar High. Admission is free. 
</P>
<P>
In its ninth season, National Pro-Am City League Assn., Inc. features teams 
that field current and former National Basketball Assn. players, as well as 
talent from the Continental Basketball Assn., Europe and the collegiate level. 
National Pro-Am recently left the direction of the NBA to become an 
independent, nonprofit corporation. Among its objectives is to provide training 
in the areas of administration, coaching, officiating, athletic training and 
game operations. 
</P>
<P>
Past participants in the league have included Magic Johnson, Isiah Thomas, Mark 
Jackson, Alex English, Karl Malone and Dominique Wilkins. 
</P>
