VIETNAM'S POPULATION EXCEEDS 64 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BANGKOK, Thailand 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vietnam announced that its population has grown to 64.4 million, and it called 
on all families to have no more than two children. 
</P>
<P>
The official Vietnam News Agency said the population had grown by 11.7 million 
since the last census in 1979, representing a high annual growth rate of 2.13%. 
</P>
<P>
An editorial in the Communist Party's newspaper, Nhan Dan, urged all people to 
observe the national target of one or two children per family, the agency said. 
</P>
