<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN DEATH OF ROOMMATE IN LLANO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man described as "an old desert rat" was arrested Friday at his home in the 
Antelope Valley community of Llano on a charge of murder in the death last 
month of his roommate, a Los Angeles County sheriff's deputy said. 
</P>
<P>
Ralph Greathouse, 63, was arrested in connection with the June 17 shooting 
death of Paul Staten, 47, who died after an argument between the two men, 
Deputy Hal Grant said. Greathouse was being held without bail at the Antelope 
Valley sheriff's station. 
</P>
<P>
Greathouse was arrested the day of the shooting, but released the next day 
because investigators thought that the shooting might have been accidental. 
</P>
<P>
Grant said the Antelope Valley office of the Los Angeles County district 
attorney decided Friday to pursue murder charges against Greathouse. He was 
arrested without incident at his home near California 18 and 233rd Street. 
</P>
<P>
A sergeant at the Antelope Valley sheriff's station described Greathouse as "an 
old desert rat" who sometimes sat in a rocking chair beside the highway waving 
at motorists. 
