<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The National Collegiate Athletic Assn. Division I Basketball Committee 
recommended awarding the men's Final Four to four cities in the years 1994 
through 1997. 
</P>
<P>
The 1994 Final Four would go to Charlotte, N.C., followed by Seattle, the 
Meadowlands in New Jersey and Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
The recommendations must be approved by the NCAA Division I championship 
committee and the NCAA executive committee, which meet Aug. 14-15. 
</P>
<P>
Cedric Dempsey, chairman of the basketball committee, said the unprecedented 
step of selecting four cities at once was taken because of the cost involved in 
making presentations. 
</P>
