<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOEMAKER WILL MAKE HIS LAST RIDE AS PART OF STRUB STAKES PROGRAM FEB. 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Next Feb. 4, the day Santa Anita runs the Charles H. Strub Stakes, will be when 
Bill Shoemaker makes his last ride. 
</P>
<P>
Shoemaker, 58 next month, has been riding since 1949, and by bowing out next 
year he will be able to do what no other jockey has done -- ride in six 
decades. 
</P>
<P>
Shoemaker, who has ridden more than 8,800 winners, announced his impending 
retirement earlier this year and is on a farewell tour that has taken him to 
many of the tracks in Europe. Today, he is scheduled to ride at Phoenix Park in 
Ireland. 
</P>
<P>
On July 21, Hollywood Park will run a special evening program in its farewell 
salute to Shoemaker, who is returning from Europe earlier that week. 
</P>
<P>
Shoemaker has won the Strub and its forerunner, the Santa Anita Maturity, seven 
times, his last win in the stake coming aboard Spectacular Bid in 1980. BILL 
CHRISTINE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
JOCKEYS; SHOEMAKER, BILL; RETIREMENT 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
