</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE THEATER FUND-RAISER THAT DISAPPEARED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Mark Pinsky's article "O.C. 'Sorcery' Fund-Raiser Goes Poof" 
(Calendar, June 15): 
</P>
<P>
I read this article with great interest, as I was one of the many psychics 
invited to volunteer my time to provide entertainment at this fund-raiser for 
the Laguna Playhouse. It was very unfortunate that the fund-raiser was canceled 
as a result of the Rev. Jerry Tankersley's letter to his congregation at the 
Laguna Presbyterian Church. It is difficult to imagine that anyone living in 
the 20th Century would refer to contemporary psychics as "those who are 
representatives and voices of spiritual powers that at times have proven to be 
destructive of human life." Tankersley and his supporters obviously have no 
idea regarding what type of services professional psychics actually provide. 
</P>
<P>
The psychic work I engage in has nothing whatsoever to do with activities 
"destructive to human life." It involves providing consulting services to the 
public in a positive and constructive manner. I frequently volunteer my 
services to organizations such as the Laguna playhouse that are engaged in fund 
raising. I know this to be true of many psychics. 
</P>
<P>
Although it would have been only beneficial for psychics to provide their 
services for the Laguna Playhouse fund-raiser, I can assure you that we do and 
will have plenty of other platform opportunities in Orange County and 
elsewhere. Tankersley and his supporters may have succeeded in canceling the 
Laguna Playhouse fund-raiser, but they won't stop professional psychics from 
providing their services to members of the public who request them. 
</P>
<P>
Tankersley and his supporters might be surprised to know that I, a practicing 
psychic, also believe in God, and I am not familiar with any psychic who does 
not. I would invite Tankersley and his supporters to read First Corinthians, 
12:4-6: "There are different kinds of gifts, but the same Spirit. There are 
different kinds of service, but the same Lord. There are different kinds of 
working, but the same God works all of them in all men." 
</P>
<P>
In closing, I can't help but think of one of my favorite passages from the 
Bible: "Judge not, that you be not judged. For with what judgment you judge, 
you will be judged; and with the same measure you use, it will be measured back 
to you." 
</P>
<P>
JO MARIE LISA 
</P>
<P>
Placentia 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070889-0109 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 80162 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 8, 1989, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Orange County Life; Part 9; Page 2; Column 2 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
