ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
EXPERTS ON DEVELOPMENT TO DISCUSS GROWTH PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Experts on the development of public and private lands will discuss Orange 
County's new growth-management plan and its impact on the building industry on 
Monday in a dinner meeting at the Red Lion Inn in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Topics to be discussed during the program, which starts at 7 p.m., include how 
the growth plan will affect the county's 28 cities and why the building 
industry is not fighting it. 
</P>
<P>
Speakers are Michael Ruane, planning director for Orange County; Phillip 
Bettencourt, an independent real estate public affairs consultant; Kathryn G. 
Thompson, president of a development company; Barry Gross, who represents 
Orange County Supervisor Gaddi H. Vasquez on the county's development 
processing review committee, and John Erskine, a partner of the development law 
firm of Nossaman Guthner Knox &amp; Elliott and a city councilman in Huntington 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
For more information or to make reservations, call the Building Industry Assn. 
at (714) 547-3042. 
</P>
</TEXT>
