<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
PROFESSOR TO SPEAK ON DEMOCRACY IN CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zheng-yuan Fu, a visiting professor in UC Irvine's department of politics and 
society, will talk on "China's Bid for Democracy -- The Plan That Failed" at a 
meeting of the Democratic 69th Assembly District on July 19. 
</P>
<P>
Fu, who also is a professor at the Chinese Academy, was imprisoned for many 
years during the Cultural Revolution. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be at 7 p.m. at the University Community Assn. Clubhouse, 4530 
Sandburg Way, Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting is free and open to the public. More information may be obtained by 
calling (714) 786-8481. 
</P>
